TY  - JOUR
AU  - Riley, John
AU  - Zeckhauser, Richard
T1  - Optimal Selling Strategies: When to Haggle, When to Hold Firm*
PY  - 1983
Y1  - 1983/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/1885625
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 98
IS  - 2
SP  - 267
EP  - 289
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - A seller encountering risk-neutral buyers one at a time should, if commitments are feasible, quote a single take-it-or-leave-it price to each. This strategy is superior to any other for finite or infinite buyer populations, whether there is learning or the distribution of buyer prices is known at the outset, with one object for sale or many. Although haggling may offer advantages in terms of price discrimination, these gains are more than offset by the losses it generates by encouraging buyers to refuse purchases at high prices.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1885625
ER  - 



